</h2>
<header class="meta-data--container">
<div class="meta-data--item desktop-only">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon engineering"></div>
<a class="category" href="/blog/category/engineering">Engineering</a>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<img class="meta-data--icon" src="https://gravatar.com/avatar/fb22593caf24e4bb4c98d467cdd247e6?s=20&amp;d=mm" />
<a class="author" href="/team/jlong">Josh Long</a>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon calendar"></div>
<time class="date" pubdate="" datetime="2019-06-27 21:39:00.713">June 27, 2019</time>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon comments"></div>
<a class="comments" data-disqus-identifier="3731" href="/blog/2019/06/27/a-bootiful-podcast-datadog-s-jason-yee-on-observability-operations-metrics-kubernetes-language-and-more#disqus_thread">
</a></div>
</header>
<section class="blog--post desktop-only">
<div><p>Hi Spring fans! In this installment Josh Long (<a href="https://twitter.com/Starbuxman">@starbuxman</a>) talks to <a href="https://twitter.com/Datadog">@Datadog</a> ’s Jason Yee (<a href="https://twitter.com/gitbisect">@gitbisect</a>) about observability, operations, metrics, Kubernetes, language and more.</p>
